{Bugojno was a sleepy Bosnian town in the quiet Yugoslavia of Marshall Tito.
Great chess was played from 26 ii until 16 iii 1978. Main player was world
champion Karpov. A series of five biannual events had started. Principal
sponsor Slavko Radic produced typewriters and metal parts. Chess gave prestige
to Bugojno. Television devoted half-an-hour per day to the event.   One game
per round plus an extra game have been selected for each tournament.   } 1. e4
c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. g3 Rb8 4. f4 g6 5. Nf3 Bg7 6. Bg2 b5 7. a3 Qa5 $5 8. O-O b4 9.
Ne2 c4 $5 10. d4 cxd3 11. cxd3 Qb6+ 12. Kh1 $6 (12. d4 $1 {
closes the diagonal for Bg7 and keeps the material equality.}) 12... bxa3 13.
Rxa3 Bxb2 $1 14. Bxb2 Qxb2 15. Qa1 $6 (15. Ra1 Nf6 16. Nd2 {
gives more counter- play.}) 15... Nf6 16. Ned4 Nxd4 17. Nxd4 a6 18. Rc1 O-O 19.
Qxb2 Rxb2 20. Rb3 Rxb3 21. Nxb3 Bb7 22. Rc7 $2 {
This move leads to imprisonment of a rook.} ({Right is} 22. e5 Bxg2+ 23. Kxg2
Nd5 {(Ljubojevic)} 24. Kf3 $1 {and White counters.}) 22... Rb8 $1 23. Nc5 ({Or
} 23. Na5 Bd5 $1) 23... Bc6 24. h3 (24. Bh3 $1 e6 $1 25. Nxa6 Ra8 26. Nb4 Ne8
$1 {is insufficient too.}) 24... a5 25. g4 Ne8 $1 26. Ra7 d6 27. Nd7 Rb7 28.
Rxb7 Bxb7 29. Nb6 Ba6 30. d4 Nc7 31. d5 Bb5 32. Bf3 a4 33. Bd1 a3 34. Bb3 Na6
35. e5 Nb4 36. Nc8 Ba4 37. Bc4 dxe5 38. fxe5 Kf8 39. Nb6 Bb5 $1 {
Spassky started with a loss but would make a comeback.} 0-1

